articles.description: In the wake of Sunday's loss to the Commanders, several Bears captains spoke about player accountability and questioned certain coaching moves. DJ Moore said that while his criticism should have been kept "in-house," he didn't back down from the message.
articles.headline: Bears stand by criticism but aim to keep it 'in-house'

articles.description: While John Harbaugh said Wednesday was a "rest day" for Lamar Jackson, the quarterback was later listed on the practice report with back and knee injuries.

articles.headline: QB Daniel Jones 'frustrated' amid his, Giants' struggles
